    <description>A Chocolatey extension that provides helper functions for Chocolatey scripts (i.e. `chocolateyInstall.ps1` and `chocolateyUninstall.ps1`).

## Get-ChocolateyPackagePath

Gets the path where the Chocolatey package is currently being installed or uninstalled from.

**Usage**:

```PowerShell
Get-ChocolateyPackagePath
// => 'C:\ProgramData\chocolatey\lib\mypackage'
```

